In the Matter of the Petition of Charles Marco Goldenberg ORMOND to be Admitted as a Citizen of the United States of America. No. 441. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. June 27, 1933. Charles M. G. Ormond, in pro. per. George Z. Medalie, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Ira Koenig, of New York City, and'Ralph E. Stone, of Mt. Kisco, N. Y., of counsel), for appellee.

Before L. HAND,. AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed on authority of Subhi Mustafa Sadi v. U. S. (C. C. A.) 48 F.(2d) 1040,
